               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origDate notBefore="1400" notAfter="1487"/>
                  </origin>
                  <provenance>Origin and provenance of the manuscript are unknown.
                     <bibl><ptr target="bm:Krebs2021Kingship"/><citedRange unit="page">138–139</citedRange></bibl>
                     speculates that it might have been brought from <placeName ref="LOC3010Ethiop">Ethiopia</placeName>
                     to <placeName ref="LOC3957Jerusa">Jerusalem</placeName> by <persName ref="PRS2907Brocchi"/>
                  after <date notBefore="1484" notAfter="1485">1484–1485</date>.</provenance>
                  <acquisition notAfter="1487">The manuscript was already part of the Biblioteca Apostolica Vaticana’s collection by <date>1487</date>,
                     at which date <persName ref="PRS2907Brocchi"/> (this person may or may not be identical with the person who might have brought the manuscript from Ethiopia)
                     borrowed it for a duration of five years.
                     According to <bibl><ptr target="bm:Lefevre1942Vaticana"/><citedRange unit="page">106–107</citedRange></bibl>,
                     this makes it the Biblioteca Apostolica Vaticana’s longest-held Ethiopic manuscript. </acquisition>
               </history>
          
